
Overview of noun hem

The noun hem has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                            
1. (3) hem -- (the edge of a piece of cloth; especially the finished edge that has been doubled under and stitched down; "the hem of her dress was stained"; "let down the hem"; "he stitched weights into the curtain's hem"; "it seeped along the hem of his jacket")
2. hem, ahem -- (the utterance of a sound similar to clearing the throat; intended to get attention, express hesitancy, fill a pause, hide embarrassment, warn a friend, etc.)

Overview of verb hem

The verb hem has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                          
1. hem -- (fold over and sew together to provide with a hem; "hem my skirt")
2. hem -- (utter `hem' or `ahem')
